    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <div type="text">
                    <opener>
                        <placeName>Jermyn Street</placeName>
                        <date>Saturday</date>
                        <salute>Dear Professor Henslow</salute>
                    </opener>
                    <div type="transcription">
                        <p>It will be a great pleasure to hold the conversation you propose.</p>
                        <p>The best plan will be for you to suit your hour as most convenient to the place &amp; time when I am here. You will find me <hi rend="underline">here</hi>, in <hi rend="underline">Jermyn Street</hi>, on Monday between <hi rend="underline">12 &amp; 4</hi> - that will probably suit you best.</p>
                        <p>On Tuesday I will be here from 12 to 1/2 past 2 when I go to lecture at the Royal Institution. In the evening of that day I shall be at home until 9. when I go to Lyell's. My address of residence is 76 Upper Berkeley Street Portman Square</p>
                        <p>in haste</p>
                        <p>Yours Most Sincerely</p>
                        <p>Edward Forbes</p>
                        <p>It would certainly be best to meet on Monday.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
